        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 6:47PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 646 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from Sutherland to Petersburg.
These storms were nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Pea size hail, heavy rain, and frequent lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible. Reduced
visibility and minor flooding possible. Frequent cloud to
ground lightning strikes.

Locations impacted include...
Petersburg, Virginia State University, Sutherland, Ettrick, Matoaca,
Petersburg Airport, Church Road, Five Forks, Burgess, Addison, and
Reams.
</description>
        <instruction>Heavy rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
